            "class": "joshie.enchiridion.books.features.FeatureText",
            "properties": {
              "text": "[b]Features[/b] - [i]Text[/i]\r\nThe text feature is a simple feature. One placed it may have some default text, which you can set in the config. To edit the text simply click on the text once, it should then highlight with yellow corners instead of blue. In this mode you cannot delete the actual feature, but you can edit the text. \r\nWith the text you can use various bbcodes such as [ b ] for bold, or [ color \u003d red] to format your text. If you wish to delete the feature itself. Click on it again until it turns blue, you should then be able to delete it.\r\nYou can also use shift and + or - to increase/decrease font size.",
              "size": 1.0
            }
          },
          "isLocked": false,
          "isHidden": false,
          "layerIndex": 2
        },
        {
          "xPos": 230,
          "yPos": 20,
          "width": 176.0,
          "height": 95.0,
          "feature": {
            "class": "joshie.enchiridion.books.features.FeatureText",
            "properties": {
              "text": "If you wish to use your system text editor you can, simply shift click on the text and it should open. Once you are done editing, save and then click back anywhere in the book and it should read in the text.\n\n[i]I would advise you to also close the file after you have edited it, as it can be tricky to tell when the system is actually going to let you edit the text otherwise[/i]\n\n[ b] bold , [ i ] italics, [ u ] underline, [ s ] strikethrough, [ color\u003dred ], colors: black, dark_blue, dark_aqua, dark_red, dark_purple, gold, gray, dark_gray, blue, green, aqua, reed, light_purple, yellow, white",
