            "properties": {
              "text": "[b]Features[/b] - [i]Images[/i]\r\nImages are one of the simplest features, simply click the button and then browse until you find the one you want to insert. Please keep in mind that they will default to the size they are, so be warned when using huge images.\r\n\r\n[b]Features[/b] - [i]Buttons[/i]\r\nButtons are a fun feature, they can perform various functions. By default Enchiridion allows you to add next page, previous page, jump to page and web link arrows. With buttons you can set their hover and unhover texture, if you want to have them invisible just give them an invisible texture. ",
